main event: An object resembling a bright star with white and blue intermittent strobes was observed hovering above Lake Shelton.
interesting points: The observation lasted approximately 20 minutes and was seen through binoculars, revealing several smaller lights around the bright object., The object was reported to have reflected light, possibly from the ground or another object., Witnesses noted that the object appeared in the same general area and time as other reported sightings., The object faded away behind trees after moving slightly east., Atmospheric conditions, including clear weather and radiative inversions, may have contributed to visual phenomena.
sighted object: a bright light with smaller lights around it
witness description: Identities of the witnesses are unknown, but they may have neighbors who can corroborate the description.
